This paper deals with the problem of robust relay placement in wireless personal area networks (WPANs) with stringent quality of service (QoS) requirements. The paper focuses on 60GHz millimeter-wave (mmWave) WPANs, which are a subset of wireless networks. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). 

The paper also involves optimization problems related to relay placement, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper deals with multimedia streaming applications, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). 

Finally, the paper discusses the issue of service disruption caused by moving subjects, which can be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
